# Bug: Incorrect `showDiff` Default Value Handling in `Assertion.assert()`

## Description
The `showDiff` parameter handling in the `Assertion.assert()` method contains a logic flaw that incorrectly forces **all non-`false` values** (including `null`, `0`, `''`, etc.) to `true`.  
This happens because the current condition defaults `showDiff` to `true` for any value not strictly equal to `false`, rather than only when `showDiff` is `undefined`.

---

## Location
- **File:** `lib/chai/assertion.js`  
- **Line:** 159  
- **Method:** `Assertion.prototype.assert()`

---

## Current Behavior
```javascript
assert(_expr, msg, _negateMsg, expected, _actual, showDiff) {
  const ok = util.test(this, arguments);
  if (false !== showDiff) showDiff = true;  // ❌ Bug: converts null, 0, '' → true
  if (undefined === expected && undefined === _actual) showDiff = false;
  if (true !== config.showDiff) showDiff = false;
  // ...
}
